= SDL_ShowWindow =
Use this function to show a window.


== Syntax ==
```c++
void SDL_ShowWindow(SDL_Window* window)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''window'''
|the window to show
|}

== Code Examples ==
```c++
SDL_ShowWindow(window);
```

== Remarks ==
In SDL 1.2 you might have used ShowWindow(info.window, SW_SHOWNORMAL) for Win32. That is not needed anymore...


